{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-jsx","path":"/posts/How to set up minimal yet powerful Ubuntu/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to set up minimal yet powerful Ubuntu","time":"January 09, 2021","image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7699115044247788,"src":"/static/c86a641ecbd28c25a4e7769a2ea46ab7/2f1b1/coverart.jpg","srcSet":"/static/c86a641ecbd28c25a4e7769a2ea46ab7/fd013/coverart.jpg 200w,\n/static/c86a641ecbd28c25a4e7769a2ea46ab7/25252/coverart.jpg 400w,\n/static/c86a641ecbd28c25a4e7769a2ea46ab7/2f1b1/coverart.jpg 800w,\n/static/c86a641ecbd28c25a4e7769a2ea46ab7/0ff54/coverart.jpg 1200w,\n/static/c86a641ecbd28c25a4e7769a2ea46ab7/06655/coverart.jpg 1600w,\n/static/c86a641ecbd28c25a4e7769a2ea46ab7/097fa/coverart.jpg 1920w","srcWebp":"/static/c86a641ecbd28c25a4e7769a2ea46ab7/ccdb5/coverart.webp","srcSetWebp":"/static/c86a641ecbd28c25a4e7769a2ea46ab7/6b183/coverart.webp 200w,\n/static/c86a641ecbd28c25a4e7769a2ea46ab7/fc32b/coverart.webp 400w,\n/static/c86a641ecbd28c25a4e7769a2ea46ab7/ccdb5/coverart.webp 800w,\n/static/c86a641ecbd28c25a4e7769a2ea46ab7/9000d/coverart.webp 1200w,\n/static/c86a641ecbd28c25a4e7769a2ea46ab7/e0075/coverart.webp 1600w,\n/static/c86a641ecbd28c25a4e7769a2ea46ab7/30cf3/coverart.webp 1920w","sizes":"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"}}},"topics":["How to","Coding","Environment"]},"wordCount":{"words":73},"timeToRead":1,"html":"<h2>Burn Ubuntu onto a USB using Etcher</h2>\n<h2>Set BIOS</h2>\n<p>Disable secure boot</p>\n<h2>Boot from the USB and install</h2>\n<p>Install third-party software for graphics and Wi-Fi hardware and additional media formats</p>\n<p>Erase disk and install Ubuntu</p>\n<h2>Set OS</h2>\n<h3>Get software</h3>\n<pre><code class=\"language-sh\">sudo apt update &#x26;&#x26;\n\nsudo apt full-upgrade --yes &#x26;&#x26;\n\nsudo apt install --yes vim screen tree rename gnome-tweaks exfat-fuse exfat-utils testdisk network-manager-openconnect-gnome &#x26;&#x26;\n\nsudo ubuntu-drivers autoinstall &#x26;&#x26;\n\nsudo apt full-upgrade --yes &#x26;&#x26;\n\nsudo apt autoremove --yes\n</code></pre>\n<h3>Set the default text editor to be Vim</h3>\n<pre><code class=\"language-sh\">sudo update-alternatives --config editor\n</code></pre>\n<h3>Set Settings</h3>\n<h3>Clear dock</h3>\n<h3>Set Files</h3>\n<h3>Fix suspend loop</h3>\n<pre><code class=\"language-sh\">sudo vim /etc/default/grub\n</code></pre>\n<p>GRUB<em>CMDLINE</em>LINUX<em>DEFAULT=\"quiet splash button.lid</em>init_state=open\"</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-sh\">sudo update-grub\n</code></pre>\n<h2><a href=\"../How%20to%20set%20up%20minimal%20yet%20powerful%20coding%20environment\">Set up coding environment</a></h2>"},"previous":null,"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/posts/How to set up minimal yet powerful coding environment/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"How to set up minimal yet powerful coding environment"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"5a473ec3-6217-5078-8414-c06d9ef605ac","previousPostId":null,"nextPostId":"6ca7b641-9410-58b2-8746-7c84969a9e3b"}},"staticQueryHashes":["1003640200","893747738"]}